-- Migration 0049: put-in / take-out corrections for 5 reaches
--
-- Operator review of LIDAR-driven gradient profiles surfaced extreme-peak
-- warnings (sample > 1500 ft/mi) on these reaches. Each is being corrected
-- by moving the put-in or take-out past a non-paddleable feature (falls,
-- dam, lake outflow) that the network trace included. Pattern matches the
-- SF Wilson 0047/0048 sequence.
--
-- For each: latitude_start/end + longitude_start/end + length + geom are
-- updated atomically. Geom is truncated to the closest existing vertex to
-- the new endpoint (prefix-strip for put-ins, suffix-strip for take-outs).
-- Length recomputed via haversine sum.
--
-- Phase 2A + 2B + emit_max_gradient_migration.py needs to re-run after
-- this migration so max_gradient + gradient_profile reflect the new geom.
--
-- Idempotent: each UPDATE is gated on aw_id AND a lat/lon != check that
-- short-circuits if the value already matches.

